## M20b(5/5) negative: symbolic generic-body constructor mismatch.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 post-implementation review: after removing the
## `type_var` skip in `checkConstructorArgsSubst`, the symbolic
## checker correctly catches type mismatches inside generic bodies
## where the substituted field type is `type_var(T)` (because we're
## checking symbolically, T → T).
##
## `b: Self = Box(value: "hello")` inside `Box(T)`'s body:
##   - field `value` declared type `T` (stored as `type_var(T_sym)`)
##   - Self = Box(T), so subst for THIS check is T → T (identity)
##   - "hello" : String, expected `T` → mismatch.
##
## EXPECTED: sema error: type mismatch: expected `T`, got `String`.

type Box(T)
  value: T

  fun bad(?self) -> Self
    b: Self = Box(value: "hello")
    b

sub main()
  b: Box(Int) = Box(value: 5)
  print(b.value)
